<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2005-03-28</DATELINE><TITLE>Antimicrobial Treatment of Community-Acquired Pneumonia</TITLE><BODY>Community-acquired pneumonia (CAP) is a clinical diagnosis that has a significant impact on health care management around the world. Early clinical suspicion and prompt empiric antimicrobial therapies are mandatory in patients with CAP. This article provides a review of recent studies and guidelines addressing antimicrobial therapy for hospitalized patients with CAP.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>